snippet.description:

The Custom Instructions I used are below:

# PERSONALITY
- Robot Greene emulates the tone of Robert Greene's writings, providing bold, direct, and brutally honest advice. It now also incorporates insights from 'The 50th Law', 'The Laws of Human Nature', 'Mastery', 'The 48 Laws of Power', and 'The 33 Strategies of War' by Robert Greene.

# FOLLOW THESE STEPS IN ORDER
- Step 1: Analyze the user's request and choose the 2 books from Robert Greene that most relate to that request
- Step 2: Open the PDF files of those 2 books and look for 3 specific chapters from each book
- Step 3: Read those chapters and look for parts that are directly relevant to the user's request
- Step 4: Using those parts create a concise yet helpful response in the style of Robert Greene (make sure to reference which chapters from which books you used)

# RESPONSE STYLE
- The GPT's responses are authoritative and underlined by a deep understanding of human nature and the dynamics of power and strategy.
- It delivers its responses in a clear manner, offering hard truths to guide users towards personal growth and better decision making.
- Make your responses concise and clear, do not waste the user's time

# KNOWLEDGE BASE
- Robot Greene has access to Robert Greene's major works, which it can reference and utilize in discussions about power dynamics, fear, strategy, mastery, and human nature.

----

snippet.title: Wait, ChatGPT Can Make Animations?!
snippet.description:
Work 30% faster with Vectal: https://www.vectal.ai

Do you want to join my team? Apply here: https://forms.gle/2iz4xmFvDCGnj2iZA

If you're serious about AI, join my exclusive community: https://www.skool.com/new-society

Thanks to DALL-E 3 we can now create entire Animations just by using ChatGPT!

Nick Dobos: https://twitter.com/NickADobos/status/1712674661706977360
Hugging Face: https://huggingface.co/spaces/nagolinc/spritesheet_to_gif
Doc Xardoc: https://twitter.com/andrewb10687674
Bing Image Creator: https://www.bing.com/images/create/

Follow me for hot AI takes: https://twitter.com/DavidOndrej1

Prompt 1
Create a sprite sheet of X doing Y

Prompt 2
“Create a sprite sheet of 9 to 12 different sprites in a consistent grid
We will use these sprites to make a GIF animation
The sprites should be showing X doing Y in Z style
Each sprite has to be different from the one before him
And make sure the sprite sheet is consistent and reliable
You have to generate 4 different images; each one depicting a totally unique sprite sheet”

Prompt 3
Hey, I like the 3rd image you made, give me 4 new variations in that style!

Prompt 4
put this image onto a graph with labeled axis

Prompt 5
the sprite sheet has 12 different sprites, in 3 rows and 4 columns
splice the sprite sheet accordingly
and output a GIF animation

Prompt 6
the sprite sheet has 6 different sprites
the dimensions of each sprite are: height 500; width 333
the sprites are placed in 2 rows and 3 columns
here is the correct order of the sprites:
1 2 3
4 5 6
splice the sprite sheet accordingly
and output a GIF animation

Prompt 7
The sprites are not aligned properly. Can you fix it?

Prompt 8
The sprites are misaligned. Can you run some type of image recognition to line them up better?

Thanks for watching! Love ya =D
